			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I pull differently.  Your snare method would be too slow for me.  I like chain pulling and mezzing mobs ready to be tanked right after the first dies.  Also I add dps and buffs which improve kill speed.  I pull with Bellows, HoS, then slow mobs.  Once I get close to my camp, I land a mez.  Tank if needed on resist then try to mez again.  The experience flys this way and thats what I'm looking for.  Requiem pretty much overwrites any haste on a mob and ds is bah.  Only thing you have to worry about is Pyrilen Fury.  Its a nasty dot.
<br />

<br />
Conaden Darksong, 70 Bard
