				<td colspan="2"><span>That was a good write up.  Another thing of note:  Whenever pulling a named, do NOT let psalm drop for an instant.  I'd hate to think what would happen if I got charmed.  I know that the nameds upstairs definitely try to do &quot;Pyreline charm&quot; or some such spell.
<br />

<br />
I also generally prefer to chain pull, and have a mob in camp at all times, but sometimes that's simply too dangerous.  Certainly doable if you have a malo'er and/or a tasher in the group.
<br />

<br />
As far as run speed goes - yes, RS5 is a must, as these have about RS7 I think.  They do run significantly faster than me on long pulls when they don't stop to cast.  I like to jump as often as possible while running back to camp.  This makes me slightly faster.  Unfortunately I require levitate to avoid lagging out on stairs, so this isn't often an option.
<br />

<br />
Good luck, and show those monks how it SHOULD be done <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />.</span></td>
